@node "Intro" "MegaCD Utils / Introduction"

 @{b}Introduction@{ub}
____________________________________________________________________________

 Hi friends,
 welcome to this new release of my MegaCD Tools!!!

 MegaCD Tools were born to let me index and explore my CDs through an easy
 to  use  AmigaGuide  interface.   I got the idea from the Aminet CDs, but
 then  i've  had other inspirations (together with my great friend Maxime)
 and  so  i've  transformed a simple tool in a new, fast, great, cool file
 manager  to easily create indexes and explore CDs and HDs (but also other
 volumes or just specific directories).

                     The MegaCD Tools are:

                          @{"MegaCDtree " link "megacdtree"}
                          @{"  MegaCD   " link "megacd"}
                          @{" MegaCDgui " link "megacdgui"}
                          @{"MegaCDprefs" link "megacdprefs"}


 You can use the MegaCD Tools to explore your CD-ROMs, you can use them as
 a  file  manager,  you  can  use  them  to  create  indexes of your files
 (pictures,  music  modules,  animations,  and so on), you can use them to
 navigate  through the infinity of your dirs and sub-dirs.  You can do all
 those things through a fast and easy to use AmigaGuide interface.

 @{"MegaCDtree" link "megacdtreeusage"} is a little proggy to build a complete dir-tree of a CD-ROM, a
 volume  or  a  specific  directory.   The  dir-tree will automagically be
 converted  into  an  AmigaGuide  file and each directory of the tree will
 become a clickable field,  so you will be able to click a dir and  @{"MegaCD" link "megacdusage"}
 will  automagically  scan  it  in order to create another AmigaGuide file
 containing  all  the  files,  the  descriptions  (if  there are any), the
 possible actions and the sub-dirs contained in it.  Of course every file,
 every  description,  every action and every sub-dir will became clickable
 fields   themselves,  so  you'll  be  able  to  easily  explore  all  the
 directories in order to perform every possible action on your files.  The
 only difficult thing is probably to write this guide, so i suggest you to
 install  and run them soon.  I can assure you that these programs are the
 simplest and fastest idea ever!!!

 You'll be able to play samples and mods, view images and anims (including
 MPEG!),  read  files  (including  HTML docs!), extract (but also list and
 test,   when  possible)  lha,  lzx,  dms  and  zoom  archives  (with  the
 possibility  to  view  the  file_id.diz) or simply copy a file to another
 dir.   Moreover  MegaCD  will  associate  the  program  Multiview  to the
 unknown-format files, in order to try visualizing them through datatypes.
 Do you know something better?


                                   @{B}PirlAGA@{ub}         &         @{B}MAXIME@{ub}
                              (pirlaga@ermes.it)       (maxime@webzone.it)



 @{"Intro" link "intro"}@{"Install" link "instal"}@{"MegaCD" link "megacd"}@{"MegaCDTtree" link "megacdtree"}@{"MegaCDgui" link "megacdgui"}@{"MegaCDpref" link "megacdprefs"}@{"Limit" link "limitations"}@{"Distr" link "distribution"}@{"Credit" link "credits"}@{"Hist" link "history"}
____________________________________________________________________________
@endnode

@node "Instal" "MegaCD Utils / Installation and Requirements"

 @{b}Installation@{ub}
____________________________________________________________________________


 You  can  use  the  supplied  Installer  script just clicking on its icon
 (raccomended),  or  you  can install MegaCD Tools by hand following these
 simple steps:

 - according to the free ram (chip or fast) you have on your system,
   select a version of MegaCD and MegaCDtree. Of course the versions that
   uses the largest amount of ram are also the versions that manage the
   largest amount of files and the biggest directory trees.

   @{"MegaCD" link "megacd"}      @{B}400@{uB}Kb  --> file filez/min/MegaCD
                @{B}700@{uB}Kb  --> file filez/med/MegaCD

   @{"MegaCDtree" link "megacdtree"}  @{B}700@{uB}Kb  --> file filez/min/MegaCDtree
               @{B}1200@{uB}Kb  --> file filez/med/MegaCDtree
               @{B}1700@{uB}Kb  --> file filez/max/MegaCDtree

 - copy the selected @{"MegaCD" link "megacd"} executable to the @{B}C:@{ub} drawer of your System
   partition, copy @{"MegaCDprefs" link "megacdprefs"} to @{B}Sys:Prefs@{ub} and put the other
   files (MegaCDtree, MegaCDgui and MegaCD.guide) wherever you want.




 @{b}Requirements@{ub}
____________________________________________________________________________


 - Any 68020+ (32bit) Amiga.

 - AmigaOS 3.0+ if you wanna use requesters and datatypes.

 - Enough free ram: at least 400Kb  to use MegaCD
                             700Kb  to use MegaCDtree

 - @{b}RAM:@{ub} and @{b}t:@{ub} have to exist.

 Nothing  more.   Of course it could work on the other Amigas, but i don't
 know.   If  you have slow and old Amigas just upgrade them!  Maybe you'll
 need some extra RAM, if you're going to scan big TREEs.

 Anyway,  if  you wanna use ALL the features of the MegaCD utils, you need
 external  tools  (we  suggest  you  the  following ones, all available on
 @{B}Aminet@{ub}):

 @{B}Lha:@{ub}                   util/arc/LhA_e138.run
 @{B}Lzx:@{ub}                   util/arc/lzx121.lha
 @{B}Dms:@{ub}                   util/arc/dms111.run
 @{B}Zoom:@{ub}                  util/arc/Zoom_5_4.lha
 @{B}File_id.diz Extractor:@{ub} util/arc/DLDiz17.lha
 @{B}Modules Player:@{ub}        mus/play/DeliTracker225.lha
 @{B}Samples Player:@{ub}        mus/play/Play16_1_7.lha
 @{B}Images Viewer:@{ub}         gfx/show/ViewTEK21.lha
 @{B}Anims player:@{ub}          gfx/show/ViewTEK21.lha
 @{B}MPEG player:@{ub}           gfx/show/aMiPEG_0_7.lha
 @{B}Web Browser:@{ub}           biz/demo/Aweb.lha

 Last important thing: MegaCDtree needs MegaCD, but NOT the contrary!!!


 @{"Intro" link "intro"}@{"Install" link "instal"}@{"MegaCD" link "megacd"}@{"MegaCDTtree" link "megacdtree"}@{"MegaCDgui" link "megacdgui"}@{"MegaCDpref" link "megacdprefs"}@{"Limit" link "limitations"}@{"Distr" link "distribution"}@{"Credit" link "credits"}@{"Hist" link "history"}
____________________________________________________________________________
@endnode

@node "MegaCD" "MegaCD - The Ultimate Indexing Util"

 @{b}Welcome to the MegaCD universe!@{ub}
____________________________________________________________________________

  @{"        MegaCD - Usage         " link "megacdusage"} How to use MegaCD
  @{"    MegaCD - Preference File   " link "megacdpreff"} Edit the Config File by hand
  @{"  MegaCD - The Implementation  " link "megacdimple"} Use Megacd in your guides/scripts

 MegaCD scans a directory and produces an AmigaGuide document with contents.
 You  can click on filenames or tool buttons and automatically take actions
 on the files, according  with extensions.
 

 @{"Intro" link "intro"}@{"Install" link "instal"}@{"MegaCD" link "megacd"}@{"MegaCDTtree" link "megacdtree"}@{"MegaCDgui" link "megacdgui"}@{"MegaCDpref" link "megacdprefs"}@{"Limit" link "limitations"}@{"Distr" link "distribution"}@{"Credit" link "credits"}@{"Hist" link "history"}
____________________________________________________________________________
@endnode

@node "MegaCDusage" "MegaCD / Usage"

 @{b}MegaCD - Usage@{ub}
____________________________________________________________________________

 Here is the full syntax:

 @{B}MegaCD@{ub}  [@{i}directory@{ui}]  [TO @{i}outfile@{ui}] [@{i}all bullshits ya want to use as comment@{ui}]


 If you leave MegaCD blank, you'll have the index of current dir.
 If  you write the comment without specifying the directory to scan, MegaCD
 will try to scan the first word of the comment as it was a dir.

  @{b}TO@{ub} @{i}outfile@{ui}   is to specify an outfile name, @{b}TO@{ub} must be UPCASED, or it will
               be considered just as a part of the comment.


 You Can also use @{"MegaCDgui" link "megacdgui"}, the GUI for MegaCD. 
 MegaCDgui reads @{"S:MegaCDtree.prefs" link "megacdtreeprefs"} to know MegaCD's path.


 In the @{b}output@{ub} file you'll find some fields to click:

  @{b}FILENAME@{ub}    to make an action corresponding to the file type
              (extract it if it's an archive, view it if it's an image,
              play it if it's a music module, and so on)         
  @{b}C@{ub}           to copy the file
  @{b}D@{ub}           to read the file_id.diz (if there's any)
  @{b}T@{ub}           to test the archive
  @{b}L@{ub}           to list the content of the archive
  @{b}R@{ub}           to read a HTML file

 Moreover  MegaCD  will create a field containing the "Short:" line of  the
 .readme  (or  .rdm)  file  of  the  relative  archive, if it exists.  This
 feature  is  particularly  useful  if  you  are  going to scan directories
 containing Aminet files (and their .readme files of course!).

 Since the release  @{B}1.2@{ub}, MegaCD  is able to navigate trough subdirs, so you 
 can use it as a replacement of DirOpus! :)


 @{b}Examples@{ub}
____________________________________________________________________________

 @{B}MegaCD@{ub}  @{i}Data:Archives@{ui}  TO @{i}Ram:ArchiveList.guide@{ui} @{i}Archived Software@{ui}

   Will produce a file called Ram:ArchiveList.guide, labeled 
   "Archived Software".


 @{B}MegaCD@{ub}  @{i}Work:@{ui}

   Will browse the root dir of Work:. Just click to navigate!!


 @{"Intro" link "intro"}@{"Install" link "instal"}@{"MegaCD" link "megacd"}@{"MegaCDTtree" link "megacdtree"}@{"MegaCDgui" link "megacdgui"}@{"MegaCDpref" link "megacdprefs"}@{"Limit" link "limitations"}@{"Distr" link "distribution"}@{"Credit" link "credits"}@{"Hist" link "history"}
____________________________________________________________________________
@endnode

@node "megacdpreff" "MegaCD / The Preferences File"

 @{b}MegaCD - The Preference file@{ub}
____________________________________________________________________________


 It's located in @{b}S:@{ub} , and it's called @{b}MegaCD.prefs@{ub}.
 It contains the full paths to run the external programs.

 You can edit it by hands or with the supplied @{"MegaCDprefs" link "megacdprefs"}.

 Here's  the default file that MegaCD will create as soon as you run it for
 the very first time (change it according to your need):

@{i}
  ; Destination Directory for LHA, LZX & COPY
@{b}  ram:@{ub}
  ; Destination Volume for DMS
@{b}  rad:@{ub}
  ; Path of MULTIVIEW
@{b}  sys:utilities/multiview@{ub}
  ; Path of LHA
@{b}  c:lha@{ub}
  ; Path of LZX
@{b}  c:lzx@{ub}
  ; Path of DMS
@{b}  c:dms@{ub}
  ; Path of COPY
@{b}  c:copy@{ub}
  ; Path of ZOOM
@{b}  c:zoom@{ub}
  ; Path of FILE_ID.DIZ Extractor
@{b}  c:dldiz@{ub}
  ; Path of IMAGES VIEWER
@{b}  c:vt@{ub}
  ; Path of SAMPLE PLAYER
@{b}  c:play16@{ub}
  ; Path of MPEG PLAYER
@{b}  c:amipeg@{ub}
  ; Path of WEB BROWSER
@{b}  Amitcp:Ibrowse/Ibrowse@{ub}
  ; Path of ANIM PLAYER
@{b}  c:ppanim@{ub}
  ; Path of MOD PLAYER
@{b}  sys:progs/music/DeliTracker_II/DeliTracker2@{ub}
@{ui}

 As  you  can  imagine,  MagicCD  needs those external programs to make the
 actions  he's  designed  for.   I  think  the most important functions are
 already  implemented,  but  if  you  think  some others are needed to make
 MegaCD the best program ever, just email @{"me" link "credits"}.  ;)


 @{"Intro" link "intro"}@{"Install" link "instal"}@{"MegaCD" link "megacd"}@{"MegaCDTtree" link "megacdtree"}@{"MegaCDgui" link "megacdgui"}@{"MegaCDpref" link "megacdprefs"}@{"Limit" link "limitations"}@{"Distr" link "distribution"}@{"Credit" link "credits"}@{"Hist" link "history"}
____________________________________________________________________________
@endnode
@node "megacdimple" "MegaCD / How to Implement"

 @{b}And now, how to implement this proggy on your guides @{ub}
____________________________________________________________________________

 Just write, in your amigaguide, something like this:

\@{"Directory" link "megacd  directory  comment of the directory for megacd"}
  Comment to directory


 so  you'll  see a  button  @{b}"Directory"@{ub}  and  its  description  @{b}"Comment to
 directory"@{ub}.  When  you'll  ckick  on that button, you'll start MegaCD, and
 you'll  have the output page, with namedir and the comment @{b}"comment of the
 directory for megacd"@{ub}.


 Just try it and learn, it's really easy to do !


 @{"Intro" link "intro"}@{"Install" link "instal"}@{"MegaCD" link "megacd"}@{"MegaCDTtree" link "megacdtree"}@{"MegaCDgui" link "megacdgui"}@{"MegaCDpref" link "megacdprefs"}@{"Limit" link "limitations"}@{"Distr" link "distribution"}@{"Credit" link "credits"}@{"Hist" link "history"}
____________________________________________________________________________
@endnode

@node "MegaCDtree" "MegaCDtree / The Final Frontend"

 @{b}Let's Browse!@{ub}
____________________________________________________________________________

  @{"     MegaCDtree - Usage        " link "megacdtreeusage"} Use MegaCDtree
  @{"   MegaCDtree - Preferences    " link "megacdtreeprefs"} Edit The Preference File

 MegaCDtree  scans  a  filesystem  and produces an AmigaGuide document with
 file  tree.   Each subdir button executes MegaCD who scans and manages the
 contents of the dir.


 @{"Intro" link "intro"}@{"Install" link "instal"}@{"MegaCD" link "megacd"}@{"MegaCDTtree" link "megacdtree"}@{"MegaCDgui" link "megacdgui"}@{"MegaCDpref" link "megacdprefs"}@{"Limit" link "limitations"}@{"Distr" link "distribution"}@{"Credit" link "credits"}@{"Hist" link "history"}
____________________________________________________________________________
@endnode

@node "MegaCDtreeusage" "MegaCDtree / Usage"

 @{b}MegaCDtree - Usage@{ub}
____________________________________________________________________________

 Here is the full syntax:

  @{b}MegaCDtree@{ub}  [@{i}directory@{ui}]  [TO @{i}filename@{ui}]


  @{i}directory@{ui}   is the root directory that will be scanned.

  @{i}filename@{ui}    is the output filename (if not specified, the program
              will name it as indicated on the prefs file).

 Remember:  @{b}TO@{ub}  is case sensitive !!


 If you leave arguments blank, and you have @{i}c:requestfile@{ui} (OS 3.x),
 a nice requester will let you select the directory to scan.



 @{b}Examples@{ub}
____________________________________________________________________________

 @{b}MegaCDtree@{ub}  @{i}CD0:@{ui} 

 Will build the whole filetree of CD0:. Just click & navigate!


 @{"Intro" link "intro"}@{"Install" link "instal"}@{"MegaCD" link "megacd"}@{"MegaCDTtree" link "megacdtree"}@{"MegaCDgui" link "megacdgui"}@{"MegaCDpref" link "megacdprefs"}@{"Limit" link "limitations"}@{"Distr" link "distribution"}@{"Credit" link "credits"}@{"Hist" link "history"}
____________________________________________________________________________
@endnode

@node "Megacdtreeprefs" "MegaCDtree / The Preferences"

 @{b}MegaCDtree - Preferences@{ub}
____________________________________________________________________________


 It's located in @{b}S:@{ub} , and it's called @{b}MegaCDtree.prefs@{ub}.

 Here's  the default file that MegaCDtree will create as soon as you run it
 for the very first time (change it according to your need):


@{i}
  ; OUTPUT file Name
@{b}  ram:MegaCDtree.guide@{ub}
  ; Path of MULTIVIEW
@{b}  sys:utilities/multiview@{ub}
  ; Path of MEGACD
@{b}  c:megacd@{ub}
@{ui}


 first entry is the OUTPUT name, other lines are multiview path and megacd
 path.

 If you wanna change it, you have to edit it by hand.


 @{"Intro" link "intro"}@{"Install" link "instal"}@{"MegaCD" link "megacd"}@{"MegaCDTtree" link "megacdtree"}@{"MegaCDgui" link "megacdgui"}@{"MegaCDpref" link "megacdprefs"}@{"Limit" link "limitations"}@{"Distr" link "distribution"}@{"Credit" link "credits"}@{"Hist" link "history"}
____________________________________________________________________________
@endnode

@node "MegaCDgui" "MegaCDgui / The Smartest Interface"

 @{b}The Wonderful GUI@{ub}
____________________________________________________________________________

 Finally i did it!

 With  @{B}MegaCDgui@{ub}  you  can easily  scan your  directories  without knowing
 anything  about  the MegaCD syntax.  Just select the dir to scan with the
 proper  requester  and start the program.  You can also indicate where to
 save the output Amigaguide file and you can eventually add a comment.

 You can also run @{b}MegaCDprefs@{ub} from the menu bar.


 @{"Intro" link "intro"}@{"Install" link "instal"}@{"MegaCD" link "megacd"}@{"MegaCDTtree" link "megacdtree"}@{"MegaCDgui" link "megacdgui"}@{"MegaCDpref" link "megacdprefs"}@{"Limit" link "limitations"}@{"Distr" link "distribution"}@{"Credit" link "credits"}@{"Hist" link "history"}
____________________________________________________________________________
@endnode

@node "MegaCDprefs" "MegaCDprefs / The Ultimate Prefs Editor"

 @{b}The Preferences Editor@{ub}
____________________________________________________________________________

 If you don't wanna waste your time editing the MegaCD prefs file by hand,
 here's  a  fast  and  easy  way  to do it!  Just pick the tools you wanna
 associate to MegaCD's actions.


 @{"Intro" link "intro"}@{"Install" link "instal"}@{"MegaCD" link "megacd"}@{"MegaCDTtree" link "megacdtree"}@{"MegaCDgui" link "megacdgui"}@{"MegaCDpref" link "megacdprefs"}@{"Limit" link "limitations"}@{"Distr" link "distribution"}@{"Credit" link "credits"}@{"Hist" link "history"}
