@node "limitations" "MegaCD Utils / Limitations"

 @{b}Limitations @{ub}
____________________________________________________________________________


 - Due to AmigaGuide limitations, @{B}PATHS MUST NOT CONTAIN SPACES@{ub}.
   Eg.  Use @{i}ram:@{ui} and not @{i}"Ram Disk:"@{ui}

   MegaCDgui checks spaces in names and tells you to change them.

   MegaCDprefs checks for spaces too, so it doesn't accept bad names, but it
   doesn't  write  warning messages.  So, if you try to select some file and
   MegaCDprefs refuses it, maybe it contains some spaces.
  

 - For  memory  reasons  i  had  to compile  different versions of MegaCD  &
   MegaCDtree.

    With 700 Kb version of MegaCDtree you can scan Aminet CDs.
    With 1200Kb you can scan EARCD too.
    With 1700Kb you scan Fish CD's too, the most complex filetree i've ever 
                seen.

   A  complex  CD contains about 2000 dirs, so the limit will not be reached
   so  often.   However  don't  be  angry if some runtime error will happens
   while  scanning  very  big  filetrees!  Just execute proggy selecting one
   subdir each time.

 - Sometimes MegaCD leaves some little output file in T:, so if it's a
   big problem for you, just delete it by hand... :)

 - Music  modules  are  played JUST if the @{B}.mod@{ub}  extension is at the end  of
   their filenames, so please use filename.mod and not mod.filename.
   You can use  @{b}DELITRACKER2@{ub} ,  @{B}SMARTPLAY@{ub}  all the other modplayers that use 
   this same syntax:
     ModPlayerName  @{b}MODULE@{ub} @{I}NameOfTheModule@{UI}

 - Due to some really strange bug, this program could format the HDs  of all
   the @{B}Ram Jam@{ub} members. If you know how to fix it, please @{B}DON'T TELL ME@{ub} ..:)

 - Message to the Italian Guys:
   Raga', non m'andava di tradurre la guida in Italiano.
   Comunque e' in inglese cosi' maccheronico che si capisce al volo! :)


 However, these limitations are not so troublesome, because i've tested the
 proggy  with  all the ROOT  dirs of Aminet 14, 13, 12, 11, 10, 9, 8, 7 CDs
 and all worked correctly!


 If you find some BUG, please contact @{" me " link "credits"}, sending the output file too, if 
 there's any (and, of course, specifying your configuration!).


 @{"Intro" link "intro"}@{"Install" link "instal"}@{"MegaCD" link "megacd"}@{"MegaCDTtree" link "megacdtree"}@{"MegaCDgui" link "megacdgui"}@{"MegaCDpref" link "megacdprefs"}@{"Limit" link "limitations"}@{"Distr" link "distribution"}@{"Credit" link "credits"}@{"Hist" link "history"}
____________________________________________________________________________
@endnode

@node "distribution" "MegaCD Utils / Distribution"

 @{b}Distribution @{ub}
____________________________________________________________________________


 MegaCD  Tools  are free, but it doesn't mean that you can do whatever you
 want with them.  If you're going to use them to index some commercial CD,
 just  send me a copy.  You can upload them whenever you want (Aminet CDs,
 bbs, ftp sites, and so on), but please do not modify the archive.

 If  you  think  they're  cool (as they are) and you are a charitable guy,
 just  send  me  a  present  (a  postcard,  the  keyfile of your shareware
 program, some money, an Infinitiv Tower, a CyberVision 3D)..  ;)



 @{"Intro" link "intro"}@{"Install" link "instal"}@{"MegaCD" link "megacd"}@{"MegaCDTtree" link "megacdtree"}@{"MegaCDgui" link "megacdgui"}@{"MegaCDpref" link "megacdprefs"}@{"Limit" link "limitations"}@{"Distr" link "distribution"}@{"Credit" link "credits"}@{"Hist" link "history"}
____________________________________________________________________________
@endnode

